Specimen information

Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, suggesting possible renal impairment. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), but no evidence of infection (negative nitrites/leukocytes). These findings may indicate renal dysfunction, possibly with tubular involvement or early diabetic nephropathy. Clinical correlation and further nephrological evaluation are recommended.
